  "prompt": "Is it possible to get into Andover without a sport?",
  "response": "Yes, it is absolutely possible to get into Andover (Phillips Academy) without being involved in sports. While Phillips Academy values well-rounded students and encourages participation in a variety of extracurricular activities, including athletics, they also place a strong emphasis on academics, arts, leadership, and other non-athletic pursuits.\n\nThe admissions process at Andover is holistic, meaning they consider the whole person rather than focusing solely on one aspect of a student\u2019s application. Here\u2019s what they typically look for:\n\n1. **Academic Excellence**: Strong grades, challenging coursework, and standardized test scores (if required) are important.\n2. **Extracurricular Involvement**: This could include music, theater, debate, community service, or other non-athletic activities.\n3. **Personal Qualities**: Leadership, character, and the ability to contribute to the school community are valued.\n4. **Recommendations**: Strong letters of recommendation from teachers and counselors.\n5. **Interviews and Essays**: These provide insight into your personality, interests, and fit for the school.\n\nIf you excel in other areas and demonstrate a passion for your interests, you can certainly be admitted without participating in sports. Andover seeks students who will enrich their community in diverse ways, so your unique strengths and contributions matter most.",
